    %section 
        %h2.s4 A sandwich model emerges
        %p As we ideated on possible structures for the PDPs, the analogy of building a sandwich started to take shape. Above all, we needed the PDPs to be a balance of flexibility and consistency. We wanted users always to be able to find important information in the same place, but we also wanted to have optional sections to add more rich content to the products that needed it. We realized that just like a sandwich, the PDPs would have components that are always required, like bread and meat. But then there would be optional add-ons — lettuce, tomato, and special sauce — depending on how fancy you wanted to get. 
        %p This analogy let us have fun with the project and helped the marketing and engineering teams get on board with the idea. 
